Solskjaer: "He's [de Gea] come back focused, really determined, with a desire to show who he is. It's his 11th season and we've never stopped believing in him, and it's important that he also knows that." #mulive [mutv]
Solskjaer: "You know he's [de Gea] a top keeper, everyone loves having him behind them." #mulive [mutv]

De Gea: "I think we reacted very well after the defeat in the Champions League. We were together, we fight until the end. We said in the dressing room we came here to take the three points and we did it, so we are really, really happy." #mulive [mu]

De Gea: "They make the change [Noble coming on as a sub] so it was a little bit strange. At the end, I make the save, take the three points, a massive three points for us, so I'm very, very happy." #mulive [mutv]
De Gea: "It was a bit crazy at the end, a great goal of Jesse [Lingard], a stupid penalty, lucky penalty for them at the end of the game." #mulive [mutv]

Solskjaer: "It was better in the second half and a great response, that was a big thing for me – how do you react when you go 1-0 down? It was a very, very good five minutes for us." #mulive [mu] https://t.co/tVbaAPjyIv

Solskjaer: "I’ve spoken about how you can’t take rests when you defend. We dropped into a back six [for the goal] and there were too many spaces. We were too late to charge the ball. We’ve already sorted that and spoke about that at half-time." #mulive [mu]
Solskjaer: "We have to work better defensively, no doubt. In the first half, we were too easy to play through. We will work on it because there is no respite when you play football." #mulive [mu]

Solskjaer: "We deserved to win. I think we created some big chances, we had pressure on them, should have had a few penalties, great response when they scored, good attitude, very good away performance in a difficult cauldron; the stadium is hard here!" #mulive [mu]

Solskjaer: "The two of them [Ronaldo and Fernandes], of course, have to work together. They’ve played together for Portugal for a little while but, for me, those are top players. Ronaldo arrives in the box again – as he does." #mulive [mu]
Solskjaer: "I've seen Mark Noble score so many penalties, you did feel down and out and expected to come home with one point but luckily David [de Gea] has continued his good form." #mulive [men]

Solskjaer: "We are very happy with the win and we deserved the win. We played some very good football, created good chances, we pressed them into making loads of mistakes. Luckily, David [de Gea] saves that penalty at the end." #mulive [men]
Solskjaer: "You're up, you're down, you're up but that's football, you have to live with it and Jesse [Lingard] has learned how to deal with ups and downs in football." #mulive [mu]
Solskjaer: "I'm so happy for him [Lingard] because you know it's ups and downs in football, he was low on Tuesday, now high again." #mulive [mu]
Childhood hero 🥺 https://t.co/qhTjgSDlA6

De Gea: "I saw Rice with the ball, I was expecting him to take the penalty then I saw Noble with the ball. It was the last minute, I made the save. A massive three points for us. Going through my head was 'save the ball'." #mulive [sky]
Lingard: "I got a brilliant reception. I had a good time here but I have to move on with #mufc and do my best with United." #mulive [sky]

Roy Keane: "#mufc need to be careful. Just because Ronaldo has come to the club, everyone thinks everything is just going to fall into place. No, the players still need to step it up. But Ronaldo is still a world-class player." #mulive [sky] https://t.co/71VDS0Dg5W

Roy Keane: "Anything in the box, he [Ronaldo] is the best in the world. It was no surprise when he produced last week [against Newcastle]. But in midweek [against Young Boys], he struggled up front without decent support." #mulive [sky]
Vamos @Cristiano 💪 https://t.co/B4p1a43Igu
Cristiano Ronaldo arriving at the London stadium #mulive https://t.co/uYvS61QfXg
Solskjaer: "Jadon’s [Sancho] started the Tuesday game and we found the decision better to leave him here now and the chance to come on and make a difference if we need him to." #mulive [sky]
Solskjaer: "Scott [McTominay] and Fred of course they’re back in, they’re a partnership that we see here, we want to have their energy here today." #mulive [sky]

Solskjaer: "I don't think it's [playing in Europe mid-week] a problem this early on in this season to recover. Of course, it's a new experience for them [West Ham], we had two more extra days so we are very well prepared of course." #mulive [mutv]

Solskjaer: "At #mufc, if you lose a game it is a crisis. I don’t pay too much attention to that. We have started the season well. Just imagine what it would be like if we came here with six points (instead of 10)!" #mulive [@ShamoonHafez]

Solskjaer: "He's [McTominay] always been a physical monster and specimen. He's fit and of course we want to get him going as quick as we can. He's missed a bit of football but the operation was needed and why not put him back in?" #mulive [mutv]
Pogba: "We always say we win games in midfield. You have to control the game, this is in a stadium not easy to play against this team." #mulive [bbc]

Pogba: "There is only one way to come back [from Champions League defeat]. Hopefully today is to get a win. That is the past, we know the mistakes we did and the performance and we want to bounce back today." #mulive [bbc]
#mufc XI vs West Ham: De Gea, Wan-Bissaka, Varane, Maguire, Shaw, McTominay, Fred, Greenwood, Fernandes, Pogba, Ronaldo #mulive
Solskjaer: "Of course he [Michail Antonio] won't play against us in the league. It's a difficult place to go to with or without Antonio, he's been a top player for them." #mulive [sky]

Solskjaer: "But then you've got what I call, nippy little creative forwards who can create from nothing, players like Said Benrahma, they've signed Nikola Vlasic now, they've got Jarrod Bowen, Pablo Fornals all playing around Antonio." #mulive [sky] https://t.co/jWF2FicE7n

Solskjaer: "You see West Ham last season, with what David [Moyes] did when he came in - he's changed the whole culture. You can see that the way they play, they're physically impressive, really well organised." #mulive [sky]

Solskjaer: "Of course we sense the expectations on us this season, we sensed the circus around the Newcastle game. Everyone in Manchester, they have an opinion on football now, which is great, and that's what we want at #mufc - we want that buzz." #mulive [sky]

Solskjaer: "Yeah of course [the fans are desperate for silverware]. That's the ultimate aim, that's what we are here for, that's the history that we have and that's the legacy that we have to leave behind whenever we leave at the end." #mulive [sky]
Jones: "I’ll fight for #mufc until someone tells me, ‘Go somewhere else." #mulive [times]

Jones: "Listen, my problems are not bigger than the problems someone has to deal with in an office, I know that. But they are problems. Footballers have problems like anybody else, and maybe me talking can help players." #mulive [times]

Jones: "I’ve shared a dressing room with Rio [Ferdinand] - great professional. Loved playing with him. Great lad, good humour. Learnt so much off him. But what he said was poor. I’m not into disputes, not into arguments, and if he didn’t know, he didn’t know..." #mulive [times] https://t.co/c6l2UoJUAV

Phil Jones has since travelled to Barcelona to have microfracture surgery. It involves drilling deep holes into the knee to allow an influx of blood, rich in growth factors, which eventually turns into fibrous cartilage. [@TimesSport]
Phil Jones: “But I love playing and I’ll do anything for United. If I have to play at 60 per cent and know I can get through it, then why not?” [@TimesSport]

Phil Jones on having his meniscus removed leaving bone crunching against bone inside the joint: “For years I’d go into games thinking, ‘I shouldn’t really be playing,’ and players would look at me, see the swelling and be thinking, ‘He’s playing here?’“ [@TimesSport] https://t.co/w4ESOIrM5g

Phil Jones: “Listen, my problems are not bigger than the problems someone has to deal with in an office, I know that. But they are problems. Footballers have problems like anybody else, and maybe me talking can help players.” [@TimesSport]

Phil Jones: “We always go back to the same point: ‘Oh they’re footballers, they should be able to deal with it, they get so much money, have this lavish lifestyle.’ But take all that away, strip all that back and we’re just human beings.” [@TimesSport]

Phil Jones: “In this society we’re living in at the minute, all the racism and stuff that affects mental health — I’d just say be careful. You don’t know how it’s going to affect players: physically, mentally, emotionally.“ [@TimesSport] https://t.co/Ch6sYeyzvY
Phil Jones on blocking youngsters’ paths: “I’ll fight for United until someone tells me, ‘Go somewhere else.” [@TimesSport]

Phil Jones on his knee since completing two 90-minute appearances for United’s under-23s: “It feels almost like I’ve started my career again. I feel young — not 29 but 25 or 26 — and because I’ve missed so much football I feel I have so much left in me.” [@TimesSport] https://t.co/y9EV0A30mS

Phil Jones: “It just gave me so much confidence. To be honest, I didn’t even watch his premiere, I was just sitting there thinking about his comment, thinking, ‘He remembers it . . . someone of his magnitude remembers that.’” [@TimesSport]

Phil Jones on Sir Alex Ferguson: “I went to the premiere of his film with a few players and he came over, we shook hands and then out of the blue he said, ‘Hey, you were f*cking terrific against Real Madrid away [in 2013]. F*cking marking Ronaldo.’ [@TimesSport] https://t.co/PM1lm37HJi

Phil Jones: “When my career finishes & I’m enjoying my life & by the way I’m fortunate that I’ll be able to do that the keyboard warriors will still be in their mum’s spare bedroom, sipping Pepsi that’s flat, eating a Pot Noodle, sitting in their boxers, tweeting.” [@TimesSport] https://t.co/rnqYzn5WiY
Phil Jones on abuse: “I must be an easy target. Every footballer has a tag and unfortunately mine is, ‘Let’s have a laugh at him.’ [@TimesSport]
